  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen I attempt to migrate (deploy) a contract to the ewasm staging testnet using HDWalletProvider, truffle hangs and doesn't get past the first RPC call, `eth_getBlockByNumber`. (Without HDWalletProvider it works fine.)\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n`truffle.js`:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nvar HDWalletProvider = require(\"truffle-hdwallet-provider\");\r\nvar mnemonic = \"...\";\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  networks: {\r\n    staging: {\r\n      network_id: \"*\",\r\n      provider: () => new HDWalletProvider(mnemonic, \"http://40.114.204.83:8545\"),\r\n    },\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nChanging the network ID, etc. didn't help.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nI expect to be able to deploy a contract.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n```\r\ntruffle-demo-metacoin> truffle migrate --network staging --verbose-rpc\r\n   > {\r\n   >   \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n   >   \"id\": 3,\r\n   >   \"method\": \"eth_getBlockByNumber\",\r\n   >   \"params\": [\r\n   >     \"latest\",\r\n   >     false\r\n   >   ]\r\n   > }\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote: a `curl` against the same RPC endpoint works fine:\r\n\r\n```\r\n> curl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getBlockByNumber\",\"params\":[\"latest\", false],\"id\":3}' http://40.114.204.83:8545\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":3,\"result\":{\"difficulty\":\"0x149db5\",\"extraData\":\"0xd883010811846765746888676f312e31302e33856c696e7578\",\"gasLimit\":\"0x7a1200\",\"gasUsed\":\"0x0\",\"hash\":\"0x3fbc8acc7f01d0e0f9a4dcda77d9aaf480550491d208eb932b2a94936bf26dcd\",...}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: OS X 10.14\r\n* Ethereum client: geth\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): `Truffle v5.0.0-beta.1 (core: 5.0.0-beta.1) Solidity v0.4.25 (solc-js)`\r\n* truffle-hdwallet-provider version: `0.0.6`\r\n* node version (`node --version`): `v11.0.0`\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): `6.4.1`\r\n",
